---
description: Project-wide coding rules
globs: ["**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

- Always start with a short implementation plan before editing files.
- Never refactor unrelated modules.
- Prefer minimal diffs.
- Preserve legacy translator behavior unless explicitly asked to change it.
- Do not break existing docs under /docs.
- For backend tasks, keep implementation under /engine unless the task is explicitly about /legacy.
- When modifying legacy translator, prefer adding a CLI wrapper instead of rewriting the GUI.
- After code changes, explain changed files and provide run/test commands.
- Respond in Vietnamese for all explanations, plans, summaries, and review notes.
- Keep code, file names, commands, identifiers, and JSON keys in English unless explicitly requested otherwise.
